COMPONENT NAME: LKM SQL to MSSQL (BULK)
AUTHOR: Oracle
DESCRIPTION: - Loading Knowledge Module - Loads data from any ISO-92 SQL Source to a Microsoft SQL Server database using BULK INSERT statement. - ODI Command OdiSqlUnload is ued to extract data in a temporary file which is then loaded into target temporary Microsoft SQL Server table created by BULK INSERT statement. - When using this module on a journalized source table, the Journaling table is first updated to flag the records consumed and then cleaned from these records at the end of the interface.
REQUIREMENTS: - The option DEFAULT_DIRECTORY indicates the location of the temporary generated file. It must be accessible by both ODI Agent and the Miscrosoft SQL Server instance. UNC paths (ex: //machine_name/share_directory/...) are supported but decrease performances.
OPTIONS (Refer to the Option descriptions for more information on each option) - DELETE_TEMPORARY_OBJECTS: Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (files and scripts) after integration. - DEFAULT_DIRECTORY: Directory where the temporary data file is created. - FIELD_SEPARATOR: Field separator for records in data file. - UNICODE_SUPPORT: Set this option to True to load data in Unicode (UTF-16) character format.
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.
Temp. directory for the data file

Directory where the temporary data file is created. This directory must be a valid path on the machine running the Sunopsis Agent. Examples: - On Windows: D:\MyDatafiles\MyTemporaryFolder - On Unix / Linux: /usr/tmp
Field separator for records in data file.

Set this option to True to load data in Unicode (UTF-16) character format.
- The target Oracle database must support Unicode - Make sure column width is sufficient at target datastore for a column to hold Unicode content.
